This paper is primarily focused on object detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the design of deep neural networks for object classification, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of convolutional neural networks is a key aspect of the paper, which is also relevant to the subfield of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses experiments and results on large-scale datasets, which is relevant to multimedia (cs.MM).
